MODEL: opus

Create a new Doey skill at .claude/skills/doey-context-audit/SKILL.md that audits the FULL Doey session (grid of Claude panes) for token waste and context bloat, not just a single Claude instance.

INSPIRATION: User provided a reference 'context-audit' skill design (single-instance, 4-step: gather /context → audit categories → score → fix). We are doing a FULL REWRITE tuned for Doey's multi-pane reality rather than adapting 1:1. Doey isn't one Claude; it's a coordinated team of ~10 instances, each with its own loaded skills, tool allowlist, agent definition, and context window. A proper audit must be pane-aware and aggregate across the team.

LOCKED DECISIONS (from Boss via user):
- SCOPE: Full rewrite tuned for multi-pane reality. Treat Doey's grid as the primary subject. Single global report showing total team token spend, per-role breakdown, coordination overhead, and multi-pane fixes.
- AUTO-FIX: Auto-apply safe items (settings.json overrides, permissions.deny additions, 'doey msg clean' for stale messages). Diff-and-confirm for CLAUDE.md cuts, agent definition compressions, skill reductions.

DESIGN — the skill should cover:

STEP 1 — Pane Survey (Doey-unique):
- Enumerate all active panes via tmux list-panes
- For each pane with a Claude instance: capture role, current context %, status (BUSY/READY/FINISHED), worker assignments
- Aggregate: total team context spend, how many panes are above 60% / 75% / 90%
- Identify which panes need /compact soon

STEP 2 — Shared Overhead Audit (loaded once per pane at startup):
- Agent definitions: wc -l on every agents/*.md and agents/*.md.tmpl, flag top 5 heaviest, test each against 5 bloat filters (Default, Contradiction, Redundancy, Bandaid, Vague)
- CLAUDE.md: project root + .claude/ + ~/.claude/ + agent-memory MEMORY.md
- Skills: .claude/skills/*/SKILL.md, count lines, run bloat filters
- Hooks: .claude/hooks/*.sh — flag hooks that return stderr on success (noise enters context), count hook invocations per event
- settings.json: autocompact_percentage_override, BASH_MAX_OUTPUT_LENGTH env
- shell/doey-roles.sh: check for unused roles
- Role-specific tool restrictions in on-pre-tool-use.sh — flag any role loading tools it never uses

STEP 3 — Msg Queue Pollution Audit (learned from this session):
- Count unread messages per pane (doey msg count --to X)
- Age distribution: how many are > 24h old, > 7d old
- Router spam ratio: subjects=task_complete from router/ subjects that match known-stale patterns
- Flag: panes with >100 unread get WARNING, >1000 get CRITICAL
- Incident: this session found 15,491 unread on Boss pane — that level of pollution taxes every msg read call

STEP 4 — Task File Bloat:
- List .doey/tasks/ files, sort by size
- Flag .task files > 50 KB
- Count tasks in pending_user_confirmation backlog — they accrue forever
- Recommend cleanup targets

STEP 5 — Duplicate Rule Detection (shared rule text across agents):
- Find identical paragraphs across agents/*.md (terse communication, role responsibilities, fresh-install invariant)
- Flag clusters where same rule is copied N times when it could live in a single shared include
- Example: 'terse communication' got baked into every agent in task #518 — that's N copies of the same ~30 lines. Each agent reload eats those tokens.

STEP 6 — Scoring (team-aware):
Start at 100. Per-issue deductions:

| Issue | Points |
|---|---|
| Any pane > 75% context without compact scheduled | -10 |
| Any pane > 90% context | -20 |
| Agent definition > 300 lines | -5 each |
| Agent definition > 600 lines | -10 each |
| CLAUDE.md > 200 lines | -10 |
| CLAUDE.md > 500 lines | -20 |
| Contradictions between CLAUDE.md files | -10 |
| Per 5 rules flagged by 5-filter test | -5 |
| Missing autocompact override | -10 |
| Missing bash output override | -5 |
| Skill > 200 lines | -5 each |
| Skill > 500 lines | -10 each |
| No deny rules + bloat dirs exist | -10 |
| Msg queue > 100 unread per pane | -5 |
| Msg queue > 1000 unread per pane | -15 |
| Router spam ratio > 50% of queue | -10 |
| Duplicate rule text cluster across agents | -5 per cluster |
| Hook returns stderr on success | -3 each |
| .task file > 50 KB | -3 each |
| pending_user_confirmation > 20 tasks | -5 |

Floor at 0. Labels: 90-100 CLEAN, 70-89 NEEDS WORK, 50-69 BLOATED, 0-49 CRITICAL.

STEP 7 — Report Format (Doey-shaped):


STEP 8 — Auto-fix + Diff-confirm flow:
- Auto-apply these without asking:
  * settings.json overrides (autocompact_percentage_override, BASH_MAX_OUTPUT_LENGTH)
  * permissions.deny entries for detected bloat dirs (node_modules, vendor, etc.)
  * doey msg clean --older-than 24h (with dry-run shown first)
  * .task file archival for files > 50 KB that are in terminal state
- Diff-and-confirm these (show unified diff, ask via AskUserQuestion):
  * CLAUDE.md rule cuts
  * Agent definition compressions
  * Skill reductions
  * Duplicate rule extraction into shared includes

STEP 9 — Trigger phrases (frontmatter 'description' field):
'Audit Doey's multi-pane context for token waste and bloat. Use when user says: audit context, audit setup, audit session, why is doey slow, token waste, context bloat, audit the team, check bloat, why is taskmaster so heavy, or invokes /doey-context-audit. Scans all active panes, agent definitions, CLAUDE.md, skills, hooks, msg queue pollution, task file bloat, duplicate rule text. Returns a team-level health score with auto-fix and diff-confirm flow.'

STEP 10 — Integration with existing infrastructure:
- Reuse shell/context-audit.sh for mechanical work where it exists (wc, grep, file walking)
- If that script lacks functionality, extend it (don't duplicate logic in the skill)
- The skill is the Claude-facing interface that reads the script's output and produces the narrative report
- Script-side: bash 3.2 compat, set -euo pipefail, proper error handling
- Skill-side: clear instructions, the 5-filter test, scoring table, fix flow

DELIVERABLES:
- .claude/skills/doey-context-audit/SKILL.md (new)
- shell/context-audit.sh extensions (Doey-aware checks: pane survey, agent weight, msg queue, duplicate rules)
- Fresh-install compatible
- Add to docs/ a short usage note
- Test: run /doey-context-audit on this exact session, verify it catches:
  * Boss msg queue pollution (15,491 unread)
  * Any agents > 600 lines
  * Duplicate 'terse communication' rule across agents
  * Any pending_user_confirmation backlog (13+ tasks right now)

CONSTRAINTS:
- Bash 3.2 compatible
- Fresh-install: first run on a new Doey session must work without manual setup
- Zero network I/O
- Must not itself become a bloat source (skill file under 400 lines)
- Auto-fix actions must be reversible where possible (back up settings.json before edit, etc.)

Plan-first: this is PLANNED because it touches skill system, shell script, and needs design for the fix-flow UX. Interview + masterplan phases, Boss approval, then implementation.
